$lang['When it comes to decoding Hexadecimal, there are a few things you need to know. First, just like the decimal system, the hexadecimal system has 10 symbols (0-9) that represent numbers. However, in hexadecimal, these digits have values that are twice as large as their counterparts in the decimal system. So, while the number “10” is represented by the symbol “A” in hexadecimal, it would be equal to “10” in the decimal system.'] = 'I ka hiki ʻana mai i ka decoding Hexadecimal, aia kekahi mau mea e pono ai ʻoe e ʻike. ʻO ka mua, e like me ka ʻōnaehana decimal, ʻo ka ʻōnaehana hexadecimal he 10 hōʻailona (0-9) e hōʻike ana i nā helu. Eia nō naʻe, ma ka hexadecimal, ʻoi aku ka pālua o ka nui o kēia mau huahelu ma mua o ko lākou mau hoa ma ka ʻōnaehana decimal. No laila, ʻoiai ua hōʻike ʻia ka helu &quot;10&quot; e ka hōʻailona &quot;A&quot; ma ka hexadecimal, ua like ia me &quot;10&quot; ma ka ʻōnaehana decimal.';
$lang['Similarly, after reaching 9 in Hexadecimal (represented by “F”), we start counting again at 10 (“10”). This pattern continues until we reach 15 (“1F”), at which point we reset back to 0 and begin counting again at 16 (“20”). This might sound confusing at first, but with a little practice, it will become second nature!'] = 'Pēlā nō, ma hope o ka hōʻea ʻana i ka 9 ma Hexadecimal (hōʻike ʻia e &quot;F&quot;), hoʻomaka mākou e helu hou ma 10 (&quot;10&quot;). Ke hoʻomau nei kēia kumu a hiki i ka 15 (&quot;1F&quot;), a laila hoʻihoʻi mākou i ka 0 a hoʻomaka e helu hou ma 16 (&quot;20&quot;). Pilikia paha kēia i ka wā mua, akā me ka hoʻomaʻamaʻa liʻiliʻi, e lilo ia i mea ʻelua!';
$lang['Lastly, just like in base 10 (the decimal system), each place value of a hexadecimal number represents a power of 16. So for example, if we had the number 423004 stored as a hexadecimal value:'] = 'ʻO ka hope, e like me ka waihona 10 (ka ʻōnaehana decimal), ʻo kēlā me kēia wahi waiwai o kahi helu hexadecimal e hōʻike ana i ka mana o 16. No laila, no ka laʻana, inā loaʻa iā mākou ka helu 423004 i mālama ʻia ma ke ʻano he hexadecimal.';
