$lang['You can use hexadecimal to convert between decimal and binary values. For example, converting 10011011001010 into hexadecimal would result in 0x4F. This means that the value 4F represents the binary number 100110110010110.'] = 'Hiki iā ʻoe ke hoʻohana i ka hexadecimal e hoʻololi i waena o nā helu decimal a me nā helu binary. No ka laʻana, ʻo ka hoʻololi ʻana i ka 10011011001010 i loko hexadecimal e hopena i ka 0x4F. ʻO ia ke ʻano o ka waiwai 4F e hōʻike ana i ka helu binary 100110110010110.';
$lang['In mathematics and computer science, hexadecimal (also base 16, or hex) is a positional numeral system with a radix, or base, of 16. It uses sixteen distinct symbols, most often the symbols 0–9 to represent values zero to nine, and A, B, C, D, E, F (or alternatively a–f) to represent values ten to fifteen. For example, the hexadecimal number 2AF3 is equal, in decimal, to (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , or 10,995.'] = 'Ma ka makemakika a me ka ʻepekema lolouila, hexadecimal (ke kumu 16, a i ʻole hex) he ʻōnaehana helu kūlana me kahi radix, a i ʻole kumu, o 16. Hoʻohana ʻo ia i ʻumikumamāono hōʻailona ʻokoʻa, ʻo ka pinepine nā hōʻailona 0-9 e hōʻike i nā waiwai ʻaʻole i ʻeiwa. a me A, B, C, D, E, F (a i ʻole a-f) e hōʻike i nā waiwai he ʻumi a ʻumikūmālima. No ka laʻana, ua like ka helu hexadecimal 2AF3, i ka decimal, me (2 × 163) + (10 × 162) + (15 × 161) + (3 × 160) , a i ʻole 10,995.';
$lang['Each hexadecimal digit represents four binary digits (bits) (also called a "nibble"), and the primary use of hexadecimal notation is as a human-friendly representation of binary coded values in computing and digital electronics. For example, byte values can range from 0 to 255 (decimal) but may be more conveniently represented as two hexadecimal digits in the range 00 through FF. Hexadecimal is also commonly used to represent computer memory addresses.'] = 'Hōʻike kēlā me kēia huahelu hexadecimal i ʻehā mau huahelu binary (bits) (i kapa ʻia ʻo &quot;nibble&quot;), a ʻo ka hoʻohana mua ʻana o ka helu hexadecimal ma ke ʻano he hōʻike aloha kanaka o nā waiwai helu binary ma ka helu helu a me ka uila uila. No ka laʻana, hiki ke helu ʻia nā helu byte mai ka 0 a hiki i ka 255 (decimal) akā hiki ke hōʻike ʻia ma ke ʻano he ʻelua huahelu hexadecimal ma ka pae 00 a hiki i FF. Hoʻohana mau ʻia ka Hexadecimal e hōʻike i nā helu hoʻomanaʻo kamepiula.';
$lang['Hex is an abbreviation of Hexadecimal, which is based on a base -16 structure and is used for simplifying how instructions to computers are represented. This 16 symbols number system was developed as a means of inhibiting an 8-bit binary number, so data can be encoded into computers effortlessly. It can be imprinted and typed using two different hex digits with each hex digit demonstrating a nibble or perhaps a 4-bits format.'] = 'ʻO ka Hex kahi pōkole o Hexadecimal, kahi i hoʻokumu ʻia ma kahi kumu -16 a hoʻohana ʻia no ka hoʻomaʻamaʻa ʻana i ke ʻano o nā kuhikuhi i nā kamepiula. Ua hoʻomohala ʻia kēia ʻōnaehana helu hōʻailona 16 ma ke ʻano he mea e pale ai i kahi helu binary 8-bit, no laila hiki ke hoʻopili ʻia ka ʻikepili i nā kamepiula me ka maʻalahi. Hiki ke paʻi ʻia a paʻi ʻia me ka hoʻohana ʻana i ʻelua huahelu hex ʻokoʻa me kēlā me kēia huahelu hex e hōʻike ana i kahi nibble a i ʻole he ʻano 4-bits.';
$lang['This number system uses 16 symbols that are represented in a range from 0-9 or A-F. The 0–9 represent numbers up to nine whereas A-F is represented by the numeric 10–15. As compared to the other three types of number systems, the hexadecimal numeral system is considered to be the most effective one.'] = 'Hoʻohana kēia ʻōnaehana helu i nā hōʻailona 16 i hōʻike ʻia ma kahi ākea mai 0-9 a i ʻole AF. Hōʻike ka 0–9 i nā helu a hiki i ka ʻeiwa a ʻo AF ke hōʻike ʻia e ka helu 10–15. Ke hoʻohālikelike ʻia me nā ʻano ʻano ʻano ʻano ʻano helu ʻē aʻe ʻē aʻe, ʻo ka ʻōnaehana helu hexadecimal i manaʻo ʻia ʻo ia ka mea ʻoi loa.';
$lang['Your hexadecimal code is invalid'] = 'ʻAʻole kūpono kāu code hexadecimal';
